actor hrithik roshan starrerÂ super 30 will now be helmed by director anurag kashyap. the film has originally been directed by vikas bahl. however, after he stepped away from the film following the #metoo allegations against him, there was no one to look after the post-productionÂ work of the film. now, kashyap has confirmed that he will take care of the rest of the film, albeit without taking any credit for it.in his statement to huffpost india, kashyap said that he has taken over the film out of responsibility and only after bahl himself agreed to it. the director was quoted by the website saying, â€œat the moment i am getting womaniya (another production) started, but yes, i will be overseeing the post-production of super 30. there are at least 30 new people debuting with this film. itâ€™s just out of responsibility for the money put in production.â€he also refuted the rumours of having gone back to the same route of friendship with bahl. he said such speculations are nothing but â€œutter crapâ€. vikas bahl/ super 30 posterÂ super 30 was initially slated to hit the screens on january 25, facing a box office clash with kangana ranaut starrer manikarnika: the queen ofâ€¦

text:
#thedarkwombredemption is 1-year old and i am still amazed that i am now a published author. i battled with sharing this book for many reasons, but i had to and it was not easy emotionally. i thank each and everyone of you who supported. the feedback has been mind blowing. thank you for trusting me. part 2 is almost finished and i will not be silent about generational abuse and womb trauma. in celebration of my anniversary, i am offering free shipping this month. you can purchase on www.craftswombman.com or at the pan african connection bookstore. please continue to support!

i was born and brought up in the us and was lucky to have had so many privileges growing up. however, not everyone is as lucky and that is something i realized early on in life. hence, i started â€œgyaan gharâ€ learning centre at the age of 15, which is a tutoring centre located in ludhiana, punjab that provides extracurricular instructions to low-income students in new lajpat nagar. while growing up in the us, i used to arrange a fundraiser in school every year, where if each student donated 5 usd, which is somewhere around 350 indian rupees, it could help run the learning centre for an entire year! this made me realize that it doesnâ€™t take much, to just reach out and put in a little effort to help someone in some way.
we started off with 10 students and today, we have 65 students enrolled, with two full time teachers and amazing volunteers who also act like extra-curricular instructors on a daily basis. of course none of this would have been possible without my grandma who is the de facto principal of #gyaanghar and oversees the daily functioning of the centre. even at the age of 80, she does it with so much gusto and enthusiasm! it is her commitment to creating a change in the community that drives me to do the same as well.
.
after completing my graduation in economics from @harvard, i moved to india to work with @aangan_trust, a nonprofit organization dedicated to reducing child harm in the forms of trafficking, early marriage, labour, and violence. i have a deeply personal passion for working on making women and children safer. especially with the #metoo movement all around us, it feels really important to lend a voice to those who may not even have the visibility to say â€œme too.â€
.
i believe that those of us who are lucky enough to be born with privilege have a responsibility to lift others up with us.
.

text:
a snippet from "elizabeth's metoo story part 1"

if you would like to share your story please get in contact of course information will be kept annoymous if wanted ğŸ’•

elizabeth had her drink spiked twice  while there. once a lovely group of young guys and girls from ireland found her and took her back to her apartment. close call. thankfully there are still good people around. 
the second time she was not so lucky.
elizabeth had been called over to an older man sitting at the bar about a job opportunity. he asked her what she wanted to drink, he said he was the owner of the club they were in, the bartender agreed. she felt safe,said an iced tea please and continued to speak to him about possible employment.

things start to get blurry but she remembers been pawned off on a younger gentleman. he felt safe to her at that time, in her state, but she still did not feel comfortable. work conversation continued as she struggled to stand upright.
do you need a lift home? he
asked her.
no no i'm fine, she insisted.
who was she kidding she could barely stand nevermind walk.
her friends were gone. where were they is all she kept thinking.
are they not wondering where i am?
they left the nightclub, the light of a new day was not creeping in, well no not creeping in, it was there, set and ready for the day.
she started to wonder what time it was,how was it this bright?

the mans car was directly outside the club. a white convertible. she remembers little details. he told her to get in, she did after refusing multiple times. feeling scared and helpless she eventually agreed.
she was still fighting the urge to pass out... they passed the so called club, closed. over he went to an apartment. elizabeth is getting a bit irate now. he calms her down, it's joint with all the staff you will love them. she knew it was a lie but she knew she had to be smart about this to get out alive. her head is in overdrive trying to stay awake and functional and trying to come up with a plan while been led to that apartment block. while been led towards that building she knew she had a fight on her hands, and if she was lucky enough to get out of there alive nothing would ever be the same....
name: She Is Tangled, Not Tamed

welcome @jowenmagturo of @palmaelash to the women of so cal family â£ï¸
_
she is a young female entrepreneur; a lash artist and teacher. she is hardworking, talented and kind.
_
jowen got started as an entrepreneur very unexpectantly. she was scrolling on ig and thought itâ€™d be cool to get her lash certification. she asked herself, â€œwhat if i became one?â€ after consulting with her parents, they advised her not to make the investment. 
_
jowen did it anyways. she booked her first client two days after completing her lash certification. in preparation, she stayed up all night researching technique and practicing. as a result of her hard work and late nights she has a thriving business and she was able to pay off her lash certification within the first month. 
_
her biggest influences are her parents and she works hard to show them that success is possible outside of a 9-5 everyday. they cautioned her against her initial investment in her business and now they are her biggest supporters. 
_
her big dream is to bring together a group of dentists to travel the world and offer free dentistry to children in need. her original plan was to become a dentist, however now she is looking to create community and change the world in a different way. sometimes, our plans change and itâ€™s important to shift with them. 
_
there are many challenges within entrepreneurship. jowen originally didnâ€™t have a place to set up, however was creative and temporarily used her momâ€™s daycare room. she is also learned how to communicate and keep boundaries in her business. 
_
@jowenmagturo is no longer an employee, but a business woman

.

.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). #muslimahnews #muslimahnewsid

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
"then there's me, i'm seventeen
and looking for a fight
all my life i was never there
just a ghost running scared
here our dreams aren't made-
they're won.
lost in the city of angels
down in the comfort of strangers
i found myself in the fire burned hills
in the land of a billion lights
bought my fate straight from hell
second sight has paid off well
for a mother, a brother and me"
#30secondstomars #cityofangels #worldwifeweb #metoo

iâ€™ve hesitated making this post but i feel very strongly it needs to be said. 
today i found out i was involved in a crime. in my local area a man has been going around for months inappropriately filming women in supermarkets. never in a million years did i think this would involve me but today i found out it does. i was devastated. i was mortified. i was embarrassed. i was inconsolably upset. but i instantly started blaming myself. â€˜did i somehow make this man think it was ok to do this to me?â€™
â€˜is this my fault because i wore a dress to the supermarket?â€™ â€˜did i look provocative?â€™ stop!!!!!! i hate we are conditioned to believe that a manâ€™s perverted behaviour is somehow a womenâ€™s fault. â€˜your dress was too shortâ€™
â€˜you were too drunkâ€™
â€˜you were flirtingâ€™  no!!!!!! why are women taught they canâ€™t be too sexy?, they canâ€™t dress a certain way?, they canâ€™t show too much interest?, they canâ€™t walk home at night?, they canâ€™t, they canâ€™t, they canâ€™t. 
why do we have to live our lives based around men thinking they can do what they want? why do we have to worry about giving a man the â€˜wrong impressionâ€™? this belief system that women are somehow to blame for a manâ€™s behaviour needs to stop. 
to anyone that needs to hear this. you are not to blame â¤ï¸

continuing my research on the #metoo movement... #metoo was popularized by american actressÂ alyssa milano, onÂ twitterÂ in 2017. milano encouraged victims of sexual harassment to tweet about it and "give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem". there were other hashtags that were in use tooÂ  #youoksis, #whatwereyouwearing and #survivorprivilege. 
i think it's mind-blowing "the magnitude of the problem" that has come out since.Â  it's not just about sexual abuse - it's about all the things that we have considered normal and although we felt uncomfortable, we have put up with it.Â  it's now okay to rebrand that feeling or episode in our life as wrong and not our fault. and to call it out if it happens again.

a woman's emasculating subjugation of her boyfriend in verona cinema has been labelled "toxic femininity". the woman, sarah, 27, a designer from surry hills, was unrepentant. "of course women should receive same pay as men, but am i going to pay for a movie ticket? is that what you're asking me? i'm sooo offended! of course men should pay! what are you crazy? i'm not paying for a movie ticket! i'm the woman! he's the man! have you lost your mind?

the boyfriend was too scared to comment.

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

(and i thought: â€man, i will never ever be able to do the sameâ€ -everybody who knows me knows- math and me- well, we are no friends. never been, and never will be.)but he said to her: â€just wait, one day alicja is going to show us all what she can.â€œ well, a few years ago my uncle passed away, not even reaching the age of 50. i would love to talk to him today, and telling him, how much this situation and his words influenced my life till now. 
iâ€˜ve decided to share this with you, to show you what i can- i canâ€™t change the world completely, but i can start- somewhere. 
dear humans/ dear parents / dear uncles and aunties / dear grannies and grandpas / dear teachers- tell children that you believe in them! say it to each other, and most important- say it to yourself. 
thank you, big man for believing in me. 
dear men-you are as much important as us- we donâ€™t want â€to stand over youâ€, we want you to stand beside us !#feminismisaboutequality 
almost three years ago i started an acting school, and i met two men, who reminded me of my uncle, because they believed in me, from the very beginning. they encouraged me to not being afraid to leave my comfort zones and to explore every side of myself and that there is nothing you should be ashamed of. 
thanks to my first acting teacher @mojohn1214  and my principal @loubinder 
without you i wouldnâ€™t be the person i am today. 
love alicja â™¥ï¸

to the ones who never made an experience like that- i am honestly sorry for you, but hating, judging, jealousy and trying to pull others down is not the right way.
finally i am able to say: #idontcarewhatyouthinkâ€œ
wish you all the best âœ¨ â €â €

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

for all the interviews i gave for the festival yesterday, i mentioned only one thing. that time and time again, pakistan surprises me to a point where my heart swells with pride. 
the #lahootimelo where humans from all backgrounds, ethnicities, religions and colour performed on the same stage, danced on the same ground and used the same bathrooms to pee (itâ€™s brings us closer ğŸ˜‚) made me feel good about calling the land of the pure my home. i felt free. i danced lots, hugged friends i hadnâ€™t seen in long and had so many people come up to me telling me they love me for everything i do. the organisers were kind, the folk musicians dressed to their best. all this far away from the more â€˜developedâ€™ â€˜progressiveâ€™ parts of pakistanâ€™s larger cities. all this in a town called jamshoro in sindh. talking about women empowerment, mental well being and proving how music brings us all closer every bloody time. pakistan, youâ€™re so bloody cute, i wish i could hold all of you in my arms and squeeze you tight right about now. #lahooti #jamshoro #anodetowomen #metoo #ibelieveher #odetowomen #lahootimelo2019

20â€ x 16â€. oil on linen. 2018

last week! iâ€™ll be giving one last walk through of the gallery this sunday february 17th at 4pm. @edwardhopperhouse 
text from the catalogue by @etcolleary â€œjoâ€™s presence in the galleries is emphatically conjured and defined by the large scale of the vibrant pools of color that cover the walls. the broad strokes and layered washes enlarged to an immersive scale are entirely in keeping with joâ€™s  outsized and ebullient personality. the fact that the lush pigment flowing floor to ceiling, on the walls of her husbandâ€™s home, was inspired by exquisite small scale works that were largely unrecognized in her lifetime is especially poignant. indeed the early pochades (small oil studies on board, most often painted en plein aire) that most clearly display joâ€™s inventive fauve palette were painted in the years before she knew edward hopper, were rarely shown in her lifetime, and are now among her most popular works. forest scene and ogunquit cliff, both dated 1914-23, were sources of inspiration for the backdrops key to fraleighâ€™s conception of the installation.â€

jo nivison hopper

edward hopper
